-- File    : 350_bronze_load_RSEG.sql
--
-- Purpose :
--   Load raw material invoice document items (RSEG) data from landing files into the
--   staging bronze layer without applying data quality transformations.
--
-- Description:
--   This script ingests external invoice document items data (RSEG) from
--   landing files generated by the bootstrap layer and persists it into
--   the staging bronze table.
--
--   The bronze layer represents the raw ingestion stage of the medallion
--   architecture. Data is loaded largely as-is, preserving original values,
--   formats, and potential data quality issues originating from source
--   systems.
--
--   Only minimal technical handling is expected (e.g. parsing, basic type
--   casting if required by the storage engine). No business validation,
--   deduplication, or referential checks are performed at this stage.
--
-- Inputs :
--   Landing files containing invoice document items data (CSV / JSON / XML),
--   produced by the bootstrap synthetic data generators.
--
-- Outputs:
--   staging.bronze_rseg
--
-- Execution Context:
--   Executed by the staging ingestion DAG after landing files become
--   available. Typically represents the first database touchpoint for
--   external transactional data.
--
-- Notes :
--   - Bronze tables should include ingestion metadata (e.g. source_file,
--     ingest_ts) to support traceability and replay.
--   - Any malformed records may be retained or redirected according to
--     ingestion policy defined in the DAG logic.
--
